Examinations are the guiding stick of university education, and students will have corresponding preparation plans for whatever kind of exams there are. Over time, this will affect the effectiveness of university education.
The Lanzhou Jiaotong University takes the student's suggestions letter very seriously and has already deployed a rectification plan throughout the school.
The English translation for the sentence is: "It is required for each teaching unit to organize teachers to carry out research and course final exams, to develop examination question papers and relevant regulations, to strengthen supervision and inspection of the question paper proposition and review process, to refine the evaluation of grades, and to strengthen the comprehensive assessment of all aspects of course teaching."
The issue of examination questions being too similar or limited in type is a matter that the university examination administration needs to address. Of course, appropriate policies need to be put in place, but the real effort should be made on a daily basis. Teachers need to have a comprehensive understanding of the teaching situation, not only understanding the teaching content, but also understanding the learning situation of students. By mastering both aspects, teaching and learning can better connect and form a positive interaction, and exams will be more in line with reality, so that both top students and struggling students can benefit.